(67, 'Custom Underwear Packaging Boxes', NULL, '<h1 style=\"line-height: 1.6;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(57, 132, 198);\">Custom Underwear Packaging Boxes</span></h1><h1 style=\"line-height: 1.6;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><o:p></o:p></span></h1>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.6;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">A couple of\r\nweeks ago, I was shopping at the mall and had to stop by a store called\r\n\"La Vie en Rose.\" The store\'s name is an indication of its target\r\nmarket: women. It\'s a lingerie store that sells bras, panties, thongs, and\r\nother undergarments. I know it sounds weird to talk about undergarments on a\r\nblog but that\'s what this post is about - custom underwear packaging boxes.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.6;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">We\'ve been\r\ngetting a lot of requests for custom underwear packaging boxes lately from\r\ncompanies looking for an alternative to the standard plastic or paper\r\nresealable bags most items are shipped in these days. Being a huge supporter of\r\nusing recyclable and/or biodegradable material for packaging, I knew that we\r\ncould provide a more environmentally friendly way to shop lingerie. As a\r\nresult, we created the Custom Underwear Packaging Box, which is made out of\r\ncompostable, biodegradable cornstarch paper.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.6;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The box\r\nitself can be easily created by printing an image onto the paper and cutting\r\naround it. However, being able to print on paper gives us a lot of options in\r\nterms of customizing it. Depending on what you want to fit in your packing box,\r\nyou can select from one of five different colors or create something completely\r\ncustom with your logo or company name printed directly on it. In addition, we\r\ncan su